### MPLS Network Action for Deterministic Networking
Presented by Xuesong Geng ([MPLS Network Action for Deterministic Networking](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-04-mpls-network-action-for-deterministic-networking-01))
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-mpls-mna-detnet](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mpls-mna-detnet/)

*   **Technical Details:** Focuses on using MNA (ISD and PSD) to support DetNet requirements (bounded latency, low loss, ordered delivery). The latest revision (v01) aligns with RFC 9994 for in-stack encoding and synchronizes with the latest post-stack header drafts. It introduces three Network Action Sub-stacks (NASs): Latency Information, Flow ID, and Sequence Number.
*   **Discussion:** No questions were raised.

