### OAM for Network Resource Partition (NRP) in MPLS Network
Presented by Liuyan Han ([OAM for Network Resource Partition (NRP) in MPLS Network](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-5-oam-for-network-resource-partition-nrp-in-mlp-network-00))

*   **Technical Details:** The draft proposes extending existing MPLS OAM mechanisms (conforming to RFC 8029) to support NRP fault monitoring. The updated version removes the "NRP resource unavailable" error code (as forwarding plane status cannot be verified by the control plane) and refines the "not supported" error code.
*   **Discussion:**
    *   **Greg Mirsky** questioned how the data plane would distinguish between data packets and OAM packets if the NRP is incorrectly configured. If NRP is broken, data packets drop, whereas OAM packets expect control plane punting. **Liuyan Han** explained they reuse existing OAM exception mechanisms (such as TTL expiration or Router Alert) to punt packets. Greg suggested defining a new Forwarding Equivalence Class (FEC) for NRP.
    *   **Zafar Ali** suggested that NRP is structurally parallel to DSCP/EXP and that operators should simply send standard OAM packets marked with specific NRP IDs rather than introducing complex new mechanisms.

