### Explicit Congestion Notification Using MPLS Network Actions
Presented by Joel Halpern ([Explicit Congestion Notification Using MPLS Network Actions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-explicit-congestion-notification-using-mpls-network-actions-00))

*   **Technical Details:** Carrying ECN in MPLS via traditional methods (RFC 5129) consumes precious Class of Service (CoS) bits. This draft proposes utilizing MNA to carry the two-bit ECN marking in both ISD and PSD structures without impacting CoS markings, supporting low-latency applications like L4S.
*   **Discussion:**
    *   **Adrian Farrel** (as an individual) confirmed that this models standard transit-to-edge ECN notification.
    *   **Xuesong Geng** supported the work for L4S deployment but asked why separate opcodes are proposed for ISD and PSD. **Joel Halpern** explained they wanted to avoid hardcoding the same opcode constraint, but they are open to unifying them.
    *   **Greg Mirsky** noted that the early IANA review feedback allows a single opcode to map to both ISD and PSD, which will be updated in the next revision.
    *   **Adrian Farrel** polled the room for document readers and encouraged more reviews.

