### Supporting In Situ Operations, Administration, and Maintenance Using MPLS Network Actions
Presented by Rakesh Gandhi ([Supporting In Situ Operations, Administration, and Maintenance Using MPLS Network Actions](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-mpls-supporting-in-situ-operations-administration-and-maintenance-using-mpls-network-actions-00))
*   **Draft:** [draft-ietf-mpls-mna-ioam](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-mpls-mna-ioam/)

*   **Technical Details:** This draft defines MPLS MNA encapsulations for IOAM option types (pre-allocated, end-to-end, Proof of Transit, and Direct Export) defined in RFC 9197 and RFC 9326. It supports both ISD and PSD options. Incremental trace is explicitly not supported.
*   **Discussion:**
    *   **Adrian Farrel** noted that the last call for this document will be coordinated jointly with the IPPM Working Group.

